title: For Sale:  Heckler & Koch SL8-1/G36 5.56/223 Converted
postcontent: (See important NOTE at the bottom)The Heckler & Koch SL8 is a semi-automatic rifle manufactured by Heckler & Koch. It is the civilian version of the Heckler & Koch G36.The rifle fires the .223 Remington or 5.56×45mm NATO cartridge and feeds from a 10-, 20- or 30-round detachable magazine. Unlike earlier types of HK rifles, it is not a roller lock bolt but rather a lug-type rotating bolt system as seen on the AR-18.As imported, the GCA required they only import the 10-rd single stack version. This rifle has been converted to accept the standard double-stack 30rd magazines and even a 100-round drum magazine. All of the original parts and magazines for the single stack version are included as well as two "wide" mags.The SL8-1 features a lightened trigger pull, adjustable cheekpiece and buttplate, and a heavier, more accurate barrel.The SL8-1 can have additional parts replaced to make it a G36. Suggest you Google the conversion for more details.Included is the gun case, two 30-round mags, one steel, the other is a PMAG. All the conversion parts, two 10-round stock single-stack mags, and a ProMag 20-round single stack mag.This is a private sale on behalf of a client.NOTE:  Due to excessive spam received in replies to the ads, primarily people phishing for email addresses, I will not reply to a response if you don't provide a phone number, or if I am unable to Google your email address and confirm it is valid.

title: For Sale:  RUSSIAN - RPK / AK converted Vepr 7.62x39 16”
postcontent: I have for sale or trade a BNIB, nice shiny and covered in oil, a Russian-made @ the Molot Plant, Trump-banned (Thanks!) in 2017, a VEPR 16” AK rifle chambered in the proper 7.62x39 cartridge. Molot Plant is the factory which produces RPK (“handheld machine gun Kalashnikov”) for the Russian military, and also the “Vepr” civilian line based on the RPK receiver and other hardware. If you DONT KNOW what VEPR is, then look it up. Compared to a Saiga, it is a much beefier AK all-around in any caliber, starting with a Thy nicker wall receiver and a heavier barrel designed to shoot a lot more rounds much faster.Vepr rifles came to US “sporterised.” They came with a rear slant-cut receiver, a beautiful cherry wood furniture with thumbhole stock and matching one piece lower handguard covering the barrel and and almost to the top of the gas tube. But it did not lend itself real easily for conversion as the parts aren’t always easy to find.So this Vepr features a Russian-made, heavy-duty like a T-34 slant-cut adapter that allows the Vepr to accept M4 MILSPEC buffertube and related hardware. The buffer tube screws deep into the adapter. The Slant-cut adapter also mounts deep into the trunion.  The Molot factory pistol grip is bolted into the mounting bracket allowing for an additional point of contact. In the Russian ad, they show a big guy doing pushups off the pistol grip while holding onto the stock and the barrel. Strong stuff.The result is a factory-looking modern AK/RPK rifle (back end).The front features a 2-piece Russian handguard retainer adapter “type VEPRtoRPK” to allow the use of genuine (real military) RPK handguards (new composite, plastic or old wood) on the Vepr rifle. The pinned muzzle cover nut was removed and a muzzle brake installed. It uses the the standard AK/AKM/RPK 14x1LH pattern and has a plunger in the front site block to index and lock in place your AK muzzle device.So, to recap - brand new, banned from import into US, Russian made and converted into RPK/AK, Vepr rifle chambered in 7.62x39. 16” heavy barrel. Russian, factory installed into left side of receiver, scope mounting “rail” compatible with AK and SVD mounts.totally reversible conversion using all Russian parts (except for MILSPEC M4 buffer tube hardware) & M4 stock. ONLY if you wanted to revert back to hunting rifle look.Bullet Guide, (installed into the front trunion) for 7.62x39 Modified Magazine Release lever - allows use of any MILITARY magazinesMolot Pistol GripRPK front handguards - new, military parts; upper and lower.Vented Gas tube with upper handguards mount - vents hot gases and dirt into the atmosphere- NOT INTO RECEIVER. Gun runs cleaner and cooler.threaded 14x1LH heavy barrel with plunger (“index/lock”) in front sight blockMILSPEC M4 6-position Buffer tube and MAGPUL stockScope mount - AK/RPK - slide into side rail; mounts any red dot or scope using picatiny or weaver mount.Red/Green Dotthis looks like it is supposed to look - a modern RPK / AK. Not a “tacti-Kool” Tapco-bolt $100 conversion. Do the research - verify what I am saying.HOW MUCH: I would like $1,350 for the rifle (magazine for display only) which is what the cost of hardware alone is. If you can find some of the parts, since Russian front/rear adapters no longer imported. I tried keeping as much “Russian” as possible without making a permanent “RPK” rifle. That is another project and not for sale.I am, however, OPEN A TO REASONABLE OFFER - I can always say no.I am also open to some trades - high end pistols - 1911, etc.  Prefer cash. Thank you for looking
